 M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/native_client/trunk/src/native_client/tests/thread_suspension/suspend_test_guest.c?r1=8936&amp;r2=8935&amp;pathrev=8936

Thread suspension: Add test to check the trusted-&gt;untrusted transition

This tests that if a thread is suspended while executing a NaCl
syscall, the syscall itself will not be suspended and the thread will
voluntarily suspend itself when returning from the syscall to
untrusted code.

I noticed that if I broke the Windows implementation of thread
suspension so that this voluntary suspension did not work, the
previous tests did not catch this.  This is why I'm adding an extra
test.

This is the first test that defines its own syscall while still using
the regular syscalls (suspend_test_guest.c uses libc so we need the
regular syscalls), so I'm changing nacl_syscalls.h to reserve a
syscall number for use in tests in general.

BUG=http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2836
TEST=run_thread_suspension_test

